info:
This content pack supports any application that follows the Apache Common Log Format (CLF). This includes, but is not limited to the following load balancers and web servers:

• Apache (HTTP Server, Tomcat)
• HAProxy (Load Balancer)
• NGINX (Load Balancer, Web Server)

IMPORTANT: While this is a complete content pack for the Apache HTTP Server and HAProxy, it is not a complete content pack for any other load balancer or web server. Again, this content pack focuses on the Apache Common Log Format (CLF), but it has been enhanced to support the HAProxy log format as well. Other content packs may recommend installing this content pack to provide addition insight into application logs.
name: Apache - CLF
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
Apache HTTP Server, often referred to as just Apache, is an open-source web server. Like many web servers, Apache leverages the Apache Common Log Format (CLF) for web request logging.

NOTE: This content pack is for informational purposes only. If you would like to monitor Apache access and/or error logs then please download the "Apache - CLF" content pack in the Log Insight marketplace.
name: Apache - HTTP Server
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
Tomcat is an open-source web server that implements several Java EE specifications. Severl Java applications that require web server capabilities leverage Tomcat. Like many web servers, Tomcat leverages the Apache Common Log Format (CLF) for web request logging.

NOTE: This content pack is for informational purposes only. If you would like to monitor Tomcat application logs for Java applications leveraging Tomcat then please download the "Apache - CLF" content pack in the Log Insight marketplace.
name: Apache - Tomcat
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
The Arista EOS content pack provides detailed monitoring and alerts for your Arista EOS devices. With the addition of the Arista Log Insight extension, additional switch monitoring beyond standard switch syslog output is available.

NOTE: To fully leverage the power of this content pack the Arista Log Insight extension needs to be installed on your switches.  Only basic functionality is available with the standard syslog settings. Please contact your Arista representative for details.

This content pack includes the following dashboards:

Overview: A high level summary of events, warnings, and errors across your network. Alerts can be triggered on emergency events that need immediate attention.

Inventory: Track the switches and transceivers currently deployed in your network.

Interface Counters / Errors: Monitor traffic statistics and interface errors.  Trigger alerts based on interface error events.

Platform Information: Track environmental data such as power and temperature. The alerts can notify an administrator of platform issues.

Virtualization: Gain visibility into VMware vMotion events and NSX logical switches on the network.

Layer 3 Routing: Monitor BGP and OSPF errors on the network.
name: Arista - EOS
author: Arista Networks, Inc.

info:
The Big Switch Networks content pack provides set of preconfigured dashboards for both physical and logical aspect of the Big Cloud Fabric. These dashboards filter and display information about physical devices on the network, such as the controller nodes and switches. The logical dashboards provide information about the logical components in the Big Cloud Fabric, such as tenants and segments.This also provides the dashboard around errors and warnings, which would help the administrator to monitor and troubleshoot the Big Cloud Fabric.

The Big Switch Networks Big Cloud Fabric content pack helps administrator with following:
- Proactive monitoring of the Big Cloud Fabric environment
  The Big Switch Networks content pack provides set of preconfigured dashboards for both physical and logical aspect of the Big Cloud Fabric. This filter the critical information and displays for proactively monitor and act on any networking events.

- Change tracking and auditing
The Big Switch Networks content pack tracks all the configuration changes through CLI, REST calls.  Keeps the audit trail for all the events.

- Helps to troubleshoot by providing the context and additional information
The Big Switch Networks content pack helps to troubleshoot any network issue by providing the additional information and the configured alerts to detect any abnormal condition in the fabric.
name: BigSwitchNetworks - BCF
author: Big Switch Networks

info:
Brocade SAN IP content pack helps the user to better search, analyse and manage the log data generated by Brocade SAN, NOS (IP) devices. Content pack can be used in two ways:
- Configure BNA to forward Syslogs from all the switches of interest to Log Insight
- Configure switches to forward Syslog to Log Insight

author: Brocade

info:
Brocade SAN content pack helps the user to better search, analyze and manage the log data generated by  Brocade SAN. Content pack can be used in two ways:

info:
The content pack for Cisco ASA offers easy to understand, visual representation on how well operationally, the ASA firewall is working. The content pack sorts the log messages collected by various firewall features for quick simple representation of messages by severity level, and the impact of these logs operationally.
 
Cisco ASA content pack collects and organizes the Log messages based upon the type and priority of the messages and stores these into the database for time of day analysis. The Log Insight system administrator can then view the log messages for researching and remediation of problems. This content pack has dashboards to display data based on firewall rules, top sources and top destinations going through firewalls, various traffic statistics for web, mail, chat and streaming data.
 
The content pack has 9 dashboards, 43 widgets and 5 alarms specific to ASA firewall. Both ASA virtual and physical appliances are supported in the content pack. Some dashboards which are specific to physical appliance may not display data for virtual appliance.
name: Cisco - ASA
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
The content pack for Nexus switches offers easy to understand, visual representation on how well operationally, the Nexus switches are working. The content pack sorts the log messages collected by feature and technology type, for quick simple representation of messages by severity level, and the impact of these operationally.
 
The Nexus Switching content pack collects and organizes the Log messages based upon the type and priority of the message and stores these into the database for time of day analysis. The Log Insight system administrator can then view the log messages by networking functions including routing, switching, security, access, authentication, as well as the more common device and interface type, for researching and remediating problems.
 
The content pack has 12 dashboards, 68 widgets, 13 queries , and X alarms specific to Nexus switches. Both Nexus fixed and modular chassis are supported including the Nexus 2K, 3K, 5K, 6K and 7K. More notable features include reporting on security, device, topology, and performance events that impact the operations of the data center network.
name: Cisco - Nexus
author: VMware

info:
The UCS content pack contains critical information about everything within a UCS system from UCS Central and UCS Manager down to chassis, blades, and networking components. The content pack provides:

Component Faults and Reasons
When hardware issues are detected, quickly investigate and resolve them.

Configuration Changes and Faults
Quickly identify what configuration changes have occurred over time and get notification of configuration faults immediately.

Authentication Requests
Track user sessions from both the GUI and the CLI including failed log in attempts and authentication sources.

The UCS content pack is a powerful monitoring tool for UCS environments, making you aware of any issues quickly and allowing you to maintain a healthy environment at all times.
name: Cisco - UCS
author: Cisco Systems, Inc.

info: This Content Pack will help you find useful nuggets in DataGravity Storage Array Logs.  You will need a DataGravity Discovery Series Storage Array with v2 firmware or later.  You can find more about installing and using the Content Pack here.
name: DataGravity - Discovery Array
author: DG Labs

info:
The Dell Networking Content Pack for vRealize Log Insight collects, filters and sorts syslog messages based on a set of pre-configured, ready to use rules for the most common operational aspects of Dell switches: Inventory, Layer 2 and 3 protocols, Interfaces, SAN protocols, as well as views to categorize logs based on the severity and resource type.

The Content Pack consists of 11 dashboards, 63+ widgets, 65+ queries, 6+ alerts and monitor more than 270+ syslog events.

The Content Pack has several panels to group widgets logically:

Inventory: Display devices, cards, ports and LLDP-discovered peers

Interface: Monitor the operational and administrative status of physical and logical interfaces, as well as error conditions

Layer 2: Track Layer 2 protocol conditions (STP, VLT, LACP, ARP, etc.)

Layer 3: Track Layer 3 protocol conditions (OSPF, BGP, ISIS, VRRP, etc.)

SAN events: Track iSCSI and FCoE/FSB protocol conditions

Hardware: Monitor environmental and operating status of the device, fan modules and power supplies, temperature and power consumption

Notes:

Follow the Setup instructions to configure VMware Log Insight and Dell switches

The Dell Networking Content Pack is compatible with Dell switches running OS9 and VMware Log Insight 3.3 or later
name: Dell Networking
author: Dell Inc.

info:
The content pack enables:

Proactive monitoring of your VMAX array
Quickly identify issues using dashboards and pre-defined alerts.

Historical viewing of VMAX events
Using the custom date functionality view VMAX trends over extended periods of times to help identify potential problems before they impact production.

Additional information and context
Each dashboard widget includes information about the widget with links to documentation or any other information that might be applicable.

The EMC VMAX content pack will help bridge the gap between the VMware and system administrators, providing a common set of data by which the VMAX can be monitored and issues addressed.

author: EMC Corporation

info:
Flash storage is an attractive method for boosting I/O performance in the data center. 
XtremIO's ground-up all-flash array design was created from the start for maximum performance and consistent low latency response times, and with enterprise grade high availability features, real-time Inline Data Reduction that dramatically lowers costs, and advanced functions such as thin provisioning, tight integration to VMware, snapshots, volume clones, and superb data protection.

This content pack offers you the ability to troubleshoot your XtremIO Flash Arrays using Log Insight and monitor your XtremIO setup for top performance.

author: ExtraHop Networks

info: The content pack created for vRealize Log Insight accepts syslog events from the Purview engine and parses out unique fields including IP addresses, port information, as well as TCP and application response times. This content pack includes three separate dashboards (Client, Application Usage, and Application Analytics) as well as several sample queries and alerts.

author: Extreme Networks

info:
The content pack for F5®  BIG-IP® provides you with information about key entities of any F5 installation’s health using  Log Insight’s ability to collect events from one or more log files.

Log Insight offers very intuitive graphical representation, especially with regards to log events. Spikes in the number and types of messages received can be flagged as events with external notifications. System administrators can drill into these events for looking at where and why these are being generated. 
 
The F5® BIG-IP® Content pack includes 8 dashboards with a total of 53 widgets and 10 alarms. The content pack enables the user to monitor the F5 server in an easily readable graphical form. It provides:
 
Events from LTM - Local Traffic Manager Logs (Pool/Node Status Info, Hardware Issues):These 2 dashboards talk of various events derived from LTM logs identified by specific error codes. It covers incidents related to node and pool status and hardware related issues like temperature, fan speed, slot id etc.

GTM - Global Traffic Manager and DNS Statistics:This dashboard group covers DNS related events such as DNS lookup failure, various events related to DNS request and response, wide IP and virtual server IP. The DNS Statistics dashboard also gives you DNS AVR and DNS global statistics of the BIG-IP system to help you manage and report on the DNS traffic on your network.

Web Access Info: Widgets in these dashboard groups provide details on the LTM traffic. The widgets are logically clubbed into 2 dashboards under this based on traffic being categorized on basis of request and response time.

AVR Statistics:  This group makes use of Application Visibility and Reporting (AVR) module to render various widgets using the analytics profile that is set up.
name: F5 - BIG-IP
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
The Log Insight General Content Pack includes four dashboards:

• Agents - Provides information about configured Log Insight agents including configured filelog and winlog collection. For information about currently configured agents, visit the Agents page.
• Security - Provides generic information about security related events including failed authentication requests and events containing user information.

author: VMware, Inc.

The Microsoft® Exchange® Server content pack includes 15 predefined Exchange dashboards, and around 76 widgets, 16 Mailbox queries, 11 Transport queries, 7 Client access and Unified Messaging queries and  around 12 Alerts for offering a more customized user experience to Exchange administrators. These dashboards provide visibility into a multitude of Exchange operation functions including Mailbox, Transport, Client Access & Unified Messaging, and Administrator Audit logs, Performance Counters, SMTP, User and Database Information, email and mailbox size statistics. Specific events offered within this Exchange content pack include the following:

• Database health checks
• Insufficient data redundancy checks
• Back pressure events
• Resource pressure events
• Critical storage errors
• Transport shutting down events
• Critical service events
• Administrative audit changes 
• Emails sent and received
• Mailbox size

The top Exchange counter information closely monitored for detecting and alerting on Exchange problems include the following:

• SMTP bytes received per message
• SMTP messages received per second
• SMTP messages sent per second
• Store driver inbound local delivery calls per second
• Store driver inbound message delivery attempts per second

Also gives an idea of various events based on the severity levels as seen in the SharePoint ULS logs.

• General Exceptions: The widgets under this dashboard enable the user to monitor various security, authentication and SP foundation related exceptions.

• Error Analysis: Errors in SharePoint logs are categorized under various severity levels such as critical, unexpected etc.
This dashboard along with 4 widgets groups the various errors based on the area, category, and process they fall under. It also includes a query widget which discusses about correlation id and events requiring administrative intervention.

• Usage Data information: This is the data about usage on SharePoint Farm, like Page requests, feature use etc. The content pack gives you usage information about feature usage, site inventory usage and page request usage by querying the various views available in the SharePoint database.

 Note: For SharePoint 2013 there would be no data seen for the dashboard Site Inventory Usage as the default view SiteInventory is not present in the database.

This also helps in monitoring the logins to the SQL server and alert the database administrator in case of multiple failed login attempts.

info:
Overview
 
The Content Pack for Oracle® Databases tailors VMware vRealize Log Insight capabilities to monitor Oracle Database Alert and Listener Logs. VMware vRealize Log Insight delivers real-time log management for VMware environments, with machine learning-based Intelligent Grouping, high performance search and better troubleshooting across physical, virtual, and cloud environments. 
 
With the Content Pack for Oracle Databases, you can apply powerful analytic-based technology to identify and solve database specific problems. The unstructured data collection capabilities of VMware vRealize Log Insight means reduced setup time and proactive management capabilities that adapt to your changing environment. 
 
Quickly expose internal database errors to your team and Oracle Support Services through real time analysis of the Oracle Database Alert and Listener Log files. The friendly interface is designed to eliminate time lost navigating log files on the command line. By leveraging the VMware vRealize Log Insight platform, the Content Pack for Oracle Databases provides accessible log management for every member of your team, and all teams in your organization. 
 
Highlights
 - Accurate monitoring of your Oracle Database installation
 - Key Oracle Database log files are covered—Alert, Listener
 
Description
The content pack for Oracle Database provides you with information about key events of a database installation’s health using vRealize Log Insight’s ability to monitor Oracle Database Logs. The content pack enables:
 
Accurate monitoring of your Oracle Database installation
Focus on known problems through monitoring events written to log files.
 
Key Oracle Database log files are covered—Alert, Listener
Six dashboards containing more than 20 widgets are included from alert and listener that go in depth to quantify your data in a multitude of manners to help diagnose problems in your Oracle database installation.
 
Minimum requirements
VMware vRealize Log Insight 2.5
Oracle Database server running one of the following versions on Linux or Windows:
 - Oracle Database 11g
 - Oracle Database 12c
 
Setup and configuration
 
1. Installation
 
To install the Oracle - Database content pack for VMWare vRealize Log Insight, follow these steps.
 
Navigate to the "Content Pack" menu in Log Insight. Select the "Import Content Pack" button. In the "Import Content Pack" menu, do the following:
 - Select the "Browse..." button and select the content pack you are trying to import
 - Select the "Install as content pack" radio button
 - Select the "Import" button
 
2. Configuration
 
The content pack requires the Log Insight agent configured using the ingestion API. To configure a Log Insight agent to forward Oracle Database events to Log Insight, follow these steps.
 
A. Listener log
Append the following to the Log Insight agent's liagent.ini configuration file and change its directory value to the path to your listener.log:
 
[filelog|ordbms_listener]
directory=/path/to/oracle/diag/tnslsnr/installation/listener/trace
include=listener.log
event_marker=^((?:Mon|Tue|Wed|Thu|Fri|Sat|Sun) (?:Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|Dec) \d{1,2} \d{1,2}:\d\d:\d\d \d{4}|\d{2}-(JAN|FEB|MAR|APR|MAY|JUN|JUL|AUG|SEP|OCT|NOV|DEC)-\d{4} \d\d:\d\d:\d\d)
tags={"product":"ora_db","product_subtype":"listener"}
 
B. Alert logs
For each database instance you will monitor on this server, append the following to the Log Insight agent's liagent.ini configuration file and change each section title's SID and directory value to that of each instance being monitored:
 
[filelog|ordbms_SID]
directory=/path/to/oracle/diag/rdbms/database/SID/trace
include=alert_*.log
event_marker=^(?:Mon|Tue|Wed|Thu|Fri|Sat|Sun) (?:Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|Dec) \d{1,2} \d{1,2}:\d\d:\d\d \d{4}
tags={"product":"ora_db","product_subtype":"alert"}
 
C. Restart the VMware vRealize Log Insight Agent service to make it start using its updated configuration file.
name: Oracle - Database
author: Blue Medora, LLC

info:
The Palo Alto Networks PAN-OS content pack provides you with powerful insight into your PAN-OS logs (currently SYSTEM, CONFIG and THREAT; TRAFFIC and HIP-MATCH will be added in a later version of the content pack).
 
Log Field Definitions
 
Each standard field for each of the log types is defined, allowing you to easily perform queries using any of the fields.
 
Field names are in the format:
 
pan_{log,system,config,threat}_fieldname
 
pan_log_fieldname is used for the fixed location fields that are common to all the log types, and includes: receive_time, serial, type, subtype and time_generated.
 
pan_{system,config,threat}_fieldname is used for a field specific to the SYSTEM, CONFIG and THREAT logs.
 
Descriptions for each field can be found "Syslog Field Descriptions" section in the PAN-OS Administrator's Guide:

https://paloaltonetworks.com/documentation/61/pan-os/pan-os/section_6/chapter_38.html

Configuring PAN-OS to Forward Logs to Log Insight

You will need to configure each firewall to forward its logs to Log Insight for analysis, or alternatively forward logs to Panorama and then forward to Log Insight.
 
To configure log forwarding to external hosts refer to the "Forward Logs to External Services" section in the PAN-OS Administrator's Guide:

https://www.paloaltonetworks.com/documentation/61/pan-os/pan-os/section_6/chapter_20.html
name: Palo Alto Networks - PAN-OS
author: Palo Alto Networks, Inc.

info:
NSX-vSphere Content Pack provides powerful filtering, logging visualization and alerting of NSX for vSphere real-time operational activities.  This enables users to effectively monitor NSX-vSphere production installations using intuitive Log Insight UI dashboard widgets with just a couple clicks.

Highlights:

Easy, at a glance, views of an entire NSX-vSphere environment and components.  Users will know at a glance whether there is a problem with a NSX-vSphere environment by simply looking at the Overview dashboard.

The Content Pack highlights many areas of a NSX-vSphere environment including:
    Common Installation / Configuration issues - exposes several targeted problem log patterns with actionable remediations 
    Logical Switch - exposes system logs, audit logs and several targeted problem log patterns with actionable remediations 
    Logical Router - exposes system logs, audit logs and several targeted problem log patterns with actionable remediations
    Distributed Firewall - contains several different dashboards to exposes firewall traffic by total aggregate traffic, hypervisors and rule Ids
    Edge Services - separates logs for Edge appliance, health check, communication agent, high availability, load balancer, firewall and Ipsec VPN services
    Edge Firewall - contains several widgets for monitoring firewall traffic

To Setup - forward all logging components to the Log Insight server including:
    1. Use the Log Insight vSphere integration to forward logs for all ESXi servers
    2. NSX-vSphere Manager
    3. NSX-vSphere Controller(s)
    4. All NSX-vSphere edge devices

Where to begin:
    The NSX-vSphere - Overview is the main entry point.  This dashboard displays all problems/alerts reflected in the entire Content Pack, therefore under normal operating circumstances the dashboard should not contain any data.  Once a log appears on a widget, read the widget's information ("i"icon) in order to navigate to the appropriate dashboard for more detailed information associated with the problem.
    Additionally the Firewall dashboards provide widgets that contain many different views of firewall data.  These visualizations are aggregated to show various slices of a NSX-vSphere environment at the hypervisor, vm and application level.

Compatibility:
    Content Pack is compatible with NSX-vSphere 6.1 +
name: VMware - NSX-vSphere
author: VMware Inc.
